2017, 2018\n|''[[Benidorm (TV series)|Benidorm]]'' \n| Malcolm/Dennis\n| 3 episodes (series 9, episodes 7 and 8 and series 10, episode 7)\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2020\n|''[[Intelligence_(British_TV_series)|Intelligence]]''\n| Barnaby Bailer\n|\n|-\n|''The Trouble with Maggie Cole''\n| Peter Cole\n|}\n\n==Advertising work==\nIn 2009 he appeared as a car salesman in a [[SEAT]] television advert. Heap voices the fox in the [[Old Speckled Hen]] adverts sponsoring comedy on [[Dave (TV channel)|Dave]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepublican.com/story.asp?storyCode=66988 |title=Old Speckled Hen renews sponsorship of Tchannel Dave|first=James|last=Wilmore|work=[[The Publican]] magazine|accessdate=15 April 2011|date=7 May 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Other acting==\nIn 2008 Heap played the role of Widmerpool in a Radio 4 serialisation of [[Anthony Powell]]'s ''[[A Dance to the Music of Time]]''. He played Eliza's husband in 2006 [[BBC Radio 4|Radio 4]] play ''The Eliza Stories'' and appeared as Marmite the Dwarf in the short-lived Radio 4 sitcom ''[[The Sofa of Time]]''. He starred in the music video for [[Four Tet]]'s single \"[[Everything Ecstatic|Smile Around the Face]]\" in 2005, contributed a multitude of character voices in the audiobook \"Do Ants Have Arseholes?\". In 2012 he starred as Martin in the [[BBC Radio 4|Radio 4]] play ''Cordite for Breakfast'', a comedy about Napoleonic-era battle re-enactments.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01kjt7r|title=''Cordite for Breakfast''|publisher=BBC|accessdate=5 December 2012|date=10 July 2010}}</ref> In March 2013, he appeared as Rincewind in a 4-part Radio 4 adaptation of Terry Pratchett's ''Eric''. He also played the angel Aziraphale in the 2014 BBC radio adaption of [[Neil Gaiman]] and [[Terry Pratchett]]'s ''[[Good Omens]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Brown|first1=Brigid|title=BBC Radio Brings Neil Gaiman and Terry Pratchett's Good Omens to Life|url=http://www.bbcamerica.com/anglophenia/2014/09/bbc-radio-brings-neil-gaiman-terry-pratchetts-good-omens-life/|accessdate=6 September 2014|publisher=BBC America|date=5 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|372423}}\n*[http://www.curtisbrown.co.uk/mark-heap/ Agency profile]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Heap, Mark}}\n[[Category:Indian emigrants to England]]\n[[Category:English puppeteers]]\n[[Category:English male film actors]]\n[[Category:English male comedians]]\n[[Category:English male radio actors]]\n[[Category:English male television actors]]\n[[Category:English male voice actors]]\n[[Category:English people of American descent]]\n[[Category:Jugglers]]\n[[Category:People from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian people of American descent]]\n", "name_user": "2a02:c7f:b05c:e800:78ed:e657:a635:f8dc", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Fixed)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mark_Heap"}
{"title_page": "National Police (France)", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=January 2008}}\n{{Infobox Law enforcement agency\n| agencyname        = National Police\n| nativename        = {{lang|fr|Police nationale}}\n| nativenamea       = \n| nativenamer       = \n| commonname        = \n| abbreviation      = \n| patchcaption      = Patch of the National Police\n| logo              = Logo-police-nationale-france.svg \n| logocaption       = \n| badge             = \n| badgecaption      = \n| flag              = \n| flagcaption       = \n| motto = Pro patria vigilant<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gouvernement.fr/gouvernement/police-nationale-une-force-d-action-et-de-protection-au-service-de-tous |title=Police Nationale - Une force d'action et de protection au service de tous |access-date=2013-06-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103084257/http://www.gouvernement.fr/gouvernement/police-nationale-une-force-d-action-et-de-protection-au-service-de-tous |archive-date=2013-11-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| mottotranslated   = \n| formedyear        = 1966\n| formedmonthday    = July 9 \n| preceding1        = S\u00fbret\u00e9 nationale (1944\u20131966)\n| employees         = 145,200 (2015)\n| volunteers        = \n| budget            = \n| nongovernment     = \n| country           = France \n| countryabbr       = \n| national          = Yes\n| map               = \n| mapcaption        = \n| sizearea          = 551,695 km\u00b2\n| sizepopulation    = 67.2 million \n| legaljuris        = \n| governingbody     = Cabinet of France\n| governingbodyscnd = \n| constitution1     = \n| police            = Yes\n| local             = Yes\n| overviewtype      = \n| overviewbody      = Direction g\u00e9n\u00e9rale de la police nationale\n| headquarters      = [[Paris]],  [[France]]\n| hqlocmap          = \n| hqlocleft         = \n| hqloctop          = \n| hqlocmappoptitle  = \n| sworntype         = \n| sworn             = \n| unsworntype       = \n| unsworn           = \n| electeetype       = Minister\n| minister1name     = [[Christophe Castaner]] \n| minister1pfo      = [[Minister of the Interior (France)|Ministry of the Interior]]\n| chief1name        = \u00c9ric Morvan \n| chief1position    = Directeur G\u00e9n\u00e9ral de la Police Nationale\n| parentagency      = \n| child1agency      = \n| unittype          = Directorate\n| unitname          = {{collapsible list |title=List of Directorates |[[Direction de l'administration de la police nationale]] |[[Direction de la formation de police nationale]] |[[Direction centrale de la police judiciaire]] |[[Direction centrale de la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 publique]] |[[Direction centrale de la police aux fronti\u00e8res]] |[[Inspection g\u00e9n\u00e9rale de la police nationale]] |[[Direction centrale des compagnies r\u00e9publicaines de s\u00e9curit\u00e9]] |[[Service de coop\u00e9ration technique internationale de police]] |[[Service de protection des hautes personnalit\u00e9s]] |[[Prefecture of Police|Pr\u00e9fecture de police]] |[[Recherche Assistance Intervention Dissuasion]]}}\n| officetype        = \n| officename        = \n| provideragency    = \n| uniformedas       = \n| stationtype       = \n| stations          = \n| airbases          = \n| lockuptype        = \n| lockups           = \n| vehicle1type      = \n| vehicles1         = \n| boat1type         = \n| boats1            = \n| aircraft1type     = Helicopter\n| aircraft1         = 0 see [[S\u00e9curit\u00e9 Civile]]\n| animal1type       = \n| animals1          = \n| person1name       = \n| person1reason     = \n| person1type       = \n| programme1        = \n| activity1name     = \n| activitytype      = \n| anniversary1      = \n| award1            = \n| website           = {{Official website|https://www.police-nationale.interieur.gouv.fr}} {{in lang|fr}}\n| footnotes         = \n| reference         = \n}}\n[[File: General Directorate of the National Police Bastille Day 2013 Paris t111638.jpg |thumb|right|[[Colour guard]] of the General Directorate of the National Police, 2013 [[Bastille Day]] parade, Paris]]\nThe '''National Police''' ({{lang-fr|Police nationale}}), formerly known as the {{lang|fr|[[S\u00fbret\u00e9|S\u00fbret\u00e9 nationale]]}}, is one of two national [[police]] forces, along with the [[National Gendarmerie]], and the main civil law enforcement agency of [[France]], with primary jurisdiction in cities and large towns. The other main agency is the military {{lang|fr|[[French Gendarmerie|Gendarmerie]]}}, with primary jurisdiction in smaller towns and rural and border areas. The National Police comes under the jurisdiction of the [[Minister of the Interior (France)|Ministry of the Interior]] and has about 145,699 employees (in April 2008). Young French citizens can fulfill the [[Civil conscription|mandatory service]] ''[[Service national universel|Service national universel (SNU)]]'' in the police force.<ref>https://www.france24.com/en/20190616-france-trial-macron-new-compulsory-national-service-teen-military</ref><ref>https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-48755605</ref>\n\nThe National Police operates mostly in large cities and towns. In that context:\n\n* it conducts security operations ([[patrol]]s, traffic control, identity checks)\n* under the orders and supervision of the [[investigating magistrate]]s of the judiciary, it conducts criminal enquiries, serves search warrants, etc.; it maintains specific services (\"judicial police\") for criminal enquiries.\n\n== Organization ==\nThe police is commanded by the director-general ({{lang|fr|directeur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral de la police nationale}}) who is currently Jean-Marc Falcone. The director-general is directly in charge of the General Directorate of the National Police ({{lang-fr|Direction G\u00e9n\u00e9rale de la Police nationale}}) (DGPN) and the immediate subordinate of the Minister of the Interior.<ref>[http://www.interieur.gouv.fr/rubriques/c/c3_police_nationale/c33_organisation ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040405062315/http://www.interieur.gouv.fr/rubriques/c/c3_police_nationale/c33_organisation |date=April 5, 2004 }}</ref>\n\nThe police is then sub-divided into (central) directorates which are composed of sub-directorates :\n\n* ''Direction des ressources et des comp\u00e9tences de la police nationale'' (Directorate of Resources and Competences of the National Police; DRCPN):<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.interieur.gouv.fr/sections/a_l_interieur/la_police_nationale/organisation/drcpn |title=Direction des Ressources et des Comp\u00e9tences de la Police Nationale / Organisation - Police nationale - Minist\u00e8re de l'Int\u00e9rieur |language=fr |publisher=Interieur.gouv.fr |date= |accessdate=2013-03-15}}</ref> fusion of the ''Direction de la formation de police nationale'' (Directorate of Training of the National Police; DFPN) and ''Direction de l'administration de la police nationale'' (Directorate of Administration of the National Police; DAPN)\n* ''[[Direction centrale de la Police judiciaire]]'' (Central Directorate of the Judicial Police; DCPJ): charged with all criminal investigations (this mission is fulfilled in the Paris area by the ''[[Direction R\u00e9gionale de Police Judiciaire de Paris]]'' nicknamed after its address \"''36 Quai des Orf\u00e8vres''\", often without the number; the national headquarters of the ''PJ'', as it is usually called in French, are actually located at 11 rue des Saussaies, in the Ministry of the Interior). The main Sub-Directorates of the Judicial Police are: \n** [[Sous-Direction Anti-Terroriste|Sous-direction anti-terroriste]] \"SDAT\" (Anti-Terrorism Sub-Directorate): elite counter-terrorist task-force.\n** [[Sous-Direction de la lutte contre la criminalit\u00e9 organis\u00e9e et la d\u00e9linquance financi\u00e8re]] \"SDLCODP\" (Sub-Directorate for the struggle against organized crime and financial delinquency): It includes all the National Investigation Offices specialized in that field, except the National Itinerant Criminality Struggle Office (managed by the [[Gendarmerie Nationale (France)|Gendarmerie Nationale]])\n** [[Sous-Direction de la police technique et scientifique]] \"SDPTS\" (Sub-directorate of forensics and crime scene investigation)\n** [[Sous-Direction de lutte contre la cybercriminalit\u00e9]] \"SDLC\" (Sub-directorate for the struggle against computer and internet crime)\n* ''[[Central Directorate of Public Security|Direction centrale de la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 publique]]'' (Central Directorate of Public Security; DCSP): patrol and response, misdemeanour investigations, emergency help; approximatively 80% of the workforce.\n**[[Groupes d'Intervention de la Police Nationale]] (Intervention Groups of the National Police; GIPN): Nine regional SWAT teams.\n* ''[[Direction centrale de la police aux fronti\u00e8res]]'' (Central Directorate of Border Police; DCPAF): performs identity checks with \"[[Directorate-General of Customs and Indirect Taxes|La douane fran\u00e7aise]]\" (official name: [[Direction g\u00e9n\u00e9rale des Douanes et Droits Indirects]]) and handles illegal immigration.\n* ''Inspection g\u00e9n\u00e9rale de la police nationale'' (General Inspectorate of the National Police, IGPN): headed by the [[Inspector General]] and responsible for [[Internal affairs (law enforcement)|internal affairs]]. In the Paris Area, these tasks are assigned to a dedicated service\u2014the ''Inspection G\u00e9n\u00e9rale des Services'' (General Inspectorate of the Services).\n* ''[[Compagnies R\u00e9publicaines de S\u00e9curit\u00e9|Direction centrale des compagnies r\u00e9publicaines de s\u00e9curit\u00e9]]'' (Central Directorate of the Republican Security Companies; DCCRS): [[riot police]], [[motorway police]], and [[mountain rescue]]; commonly referred to as the CRS.\n* ''Service de coop\u00e9ration technique internationale de police'' (Technical International Police Co-operation Service; SCTIP).\n* ''[[Service de protection des hautes personnalit\u00e9s]]'' (Important Persons Protection Service; SPHP): VIP protection such as foreign diplomats and also responsible for the protection of the [[President of the French Republic]] through the  '[[Groupe de S\u00e9curit\u00e9 de la Pr\u00e9sidence de la R\u00e9publique]]'.\n* The ''Unit\u00e9 de Coordination de la Lutte Antiterroriste'' (UCLAT; Counterterrorism Struggle Coordination Unit) and its [[Recherche Assistance Intervention Dissuasion]] (Research, Assistance, Intervention, Deterrence; RAID) unit.\n\nThe ''Pr\u00e9fet de Police'', currently [[Bernard Boucault]], under direct orders of the Minister of the Interior, manages the ''[[Paris Police|Pr\u00e9fecture de Police de Paris]]'' which includes all police and security services in [[Paris]] and neighbouring d\u00e9partements, those services not being under the control of the director-general. The police forces in the other d\u00e9partements of the [[\u00cele-de-France (region)|\u00cele-de-France]] region are under the direct command of the [[Pr\u00e9fet de d\u00e9partement|Pr\u00e9fet]] (D\u00e9partement Prefect) in charge, being himself under the supervision of the ''Pr\u00e9fet de Police'' as far as the active on-the-field police work is concerned, and under the control of the director-general for the rest.\n\n=== Former directorates ===\nAs of 1 July 2008, the following two National Police directorates:\n* ''[[Direction de la surveillance du territoire]]'' (Directorate of Territorial Surveillance; DST) \u2013 [[counter-intelligence]], [[counterespionage]], [[counterterrorism]]\n* ''[[Renseignements g\u00e9n\u00e9raux|Direction centrale des renseignements g\u00e9n\u00e9raux]]'' (Central Directorate of General Information; DCRG or RG) \u2013 police intelligence, records, research, analysis (and also policing [[gambling]] and [[horse racing]], two activities which are now in the hands of the \"Service central des courses et jeux\" SCCJ, a unit of the Judicial Police)\nwere merged into one single domestic [[intelligence agency]] titled the ''[[Direction centrale du renseignement int\u00e9rieur]]'' (DCRI). The DCRI was placed directly under the [[Minister of the Interior (France)|Ministry of the Interior]].<ref>[http://www.interieur.gouv.fr/sections/a_la_une/toute_l_actualite/securite-interieure/creation-dcri Official announcement of the DCRI's launch on the website of the French Ministry of the Interior.]</ref>\n\n== Ranks ==\nThe National Police is divided into three ''corps'', in the terminology of the [[French Civil Service]], in ascending order of seniority:\n* The ''Corps d'encadrement et d'application'' (Management and Enforcement Corps) corresponds approximately to the enlisted and [[non-commissioned officer|non-commissioned]] ranks in a military force, or to [[constable]]s and [[sergeant]]s in a [[British police|British]]-style civil police force.\n<gallery class=\"center\">\nFile:Police nationale-gardien de la paix stagiaire.svg|''Gardien de la paix stagiaire'' (keeper of the peace, intern\") 1st year after school.\nFile:Police nationale-gardien de la paix.svg|''Gardien de la paix'' (keeper of the peace)\nFile:Police nationale-Brigadier.svg|''Brigadier''\nFile:Police nationale-Brigadier chef.svg|''Brigadier-chef''\nFile:Police nationale-Brigadier major.svg|''Major''\n</gallery>\n\n* The ''Corps de commandement'' (Command Corps) corresponds approximately to the lower [[commissioned officer|commissioned]] ranks of a military force, or the grades of [[inspector]] and [[chief inspector]] in a British-style civil police force. These ranks were previously known as ''inspecteurs'' if detectives or ''officiers de la paix'' if uniformed, although [[Compagnies R\u00e9publicaines de S\u00e9curit\u00e9|CRS]] officers always used the current ranks.\n<gallery class=\"center\">\nFile:Police nationale-\u00e9l\u00e8ve lieutenant de police.svg|''Lieutenant student''\nFile:Police nationale-lieutenant stagiaire.svg|''Lieutenant intern''\nFile:Police nationale-lieutenant.svg|''[[Lieutenant#Police_rank|Lieutenant]]'' (formerly ''Officier de la paix'' or ''Inspecteur'')\nFile:Police nationale-capitaine.svg|''[[Police captain|Capitaine]]'' (formerly ''Officer de la paix principal'' or ''Inspecteur principal'')\nFile:Police nationale-commandant.svg|''[[Commandant]]'' (formerly ''Commandant'' or ''Inspecteur divisionnaire'')\nFile:Police nationale-commandant.svg|''[[Commandant]] divisionnaire''<br> <small>Same insignia as Commandant but with gold oak leaf</small>\nFile:Police nationale-commandant.svg|''[[Commandant]] divisionnaire functionnel''<br> <small>Same insignia as Commandant but with silver oak leaf</small>\n</gallery>\n\n\n\n* The ''Corps de conception et de direction'' (Conception and Direction Corps) corresponds approximately to the higher commissioned ranks of a military force, or to grades of [[Chief Superintendent (police)|Chief superintendent]] and chief officers in a British-style civil police force.\n<gallery class=\"center\">\nFile:Police nationale-commissaire.svg|''[[Commissaire de police]]'' (Chief superintendent)\nFile:Police nationale-commissaire divisionnaire.svg|''[[Commissaire divisionnaire]]'' (Ass. Chief Constable)\nFile:Police nationale-contr\u00f4leur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral.svg|''Contr\u00f4leur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral'' (Controller General) the equivalent of a D.A.C. or Assistant commissioner. In the 'provincial constabularies', this is the rank of an Chief Constable.\nFile:Police nationale-inspecteur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral.svg|''Inspecteur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral'' ([[Inspector General]]) This is the equivalent of a Deputy Commissioner in Metropolitan Police of London.\nFile:Police nationale-directeur des services actifs.svg|''Directeur des services actifs'' (Director of the Active Services) Equivalent of a Commissioner in London in a British-style police force\n</gallery>\n\nAll the ranks insignia may be worn either on the shoulders or on the chest. In the latter they are square-shaped.\n\nPrior to 1995 two civilian corps (\"Inspecteurs\" and \"Enqu\u00eateurs\") existed in which plainclothes officers were given the training and authority to conduct investigations. The closest American equivalent is the [[detective]].\n\n== Equipment ==\n\n=== Weapons ===\n[[File:DCB-Shooting SIG-SAUER 2022.jpg|thumb|[[SIG Pro|SP 2022]], the present standard issued sidearm of French police officers.]]\n\nIn 1935, the French police used a variety of side arms, both revolvers and semi-automatic pistols, notably comprising the [[MAS 1873 revolver|MAS 1873]], the [[Mod\u00e8le 1892 revolver|MAS 1892]], the [[FN M1900]], [[Ruby pistol]]s, and a variety of privately purchased weapons.\n\nImmediately after the [[Second World War]], a variety of military side arms was used, often captured weapons provided by the Army or French-produced German-designed weapons, such as the [[Mauser HSc]] or the [[Walther P38]] for sidearms, and the [[Karabiner 98k]] rifle.\n\nIn 1951, a standardisation was performed on the [[RR 51]] pistol<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.littlegun.info/arme%20francaise/artisans%20m%20n%20o/a%20mapf%20mod%20r%20gb.htm |title=Nouvelle page 0 |publisher=Littlegun.info |date= |accessdate=2013-03-15}}</ref> in [[7.65\u00d717mm]] and on the [[MAS-38]] and [[MAT-49]] for submachine guns. From 1953, in the context of heightening violence of the [[Algeria War]], CRS units were upgraded to the [[9\u00d719mm]] [[MAC Mle 1950]].\n\nIn the early 1960s, large-caliber revolvers were introduced, culminating with the introduction of the [[Manurhin MR 73]] and the [[Ruger SP101]]. In the 80s, a process to standardize revolvers was initiated. The 1970s also saw the introduction of assault rifles{{clarify|date=January 2015}} (such as the [[SIG SG 543]]) to fend off heavily armed organised crime and terrorism.\n\nIn the 2000s, the police started switching to semi-automatic pistols and to the [[9\u00d719mm Parabellum]] cartridge. For some years, the standard sidearm in the National Police and the [[Gendarmerie Nationale (France)|Gendarmerie Nationale]] was the [[Beretta 92|PAMAS G1]], which was French licensed and made. In 2003 both agencies made the biggest small arms contract since the Second World War<ref name=\"Ayoob\">Ayoob, Massad F.: ''The Gun Digest Book of SIG-Sauer: A Complete Look at SIG-Sauer Pistols'', page 80. Gun Digest, 2004.</ref> for about 250,000 [[SIG Pro|SIG Sauer Pro SP 2022s]], a custom-tailored variant of the SIG Pro, replacing the PAMAS-G1 and several other pistols in service. The weapons are planned to stay in service until the year 2022, hence the weapon name. It is possible the pistols will be used past 2022 as the agency purchased more pistols in late 2018 possibly indicating the pistols may be used beyond 2022. <ref>\nhttps://www.thefirearmblog.com/blog/2018/12/05/sig-sp2022-for-french-police/</ref>\n\n\nFor greater threats the police use slightly modified [[Ruger Mini-14]]s purchased in the 1970s.\n\nSome sources have claimed the use of the [[Spectre M4]] by the French National Police.\n\n=== Cars ===\nWhile the vast majority of vehicles are screen printed French brand (mainly Renault, Citro\u00ebn and Peugeot), some service vehicles are provided by Ford and Opel. Plainclothes officers or specialised branches use vehicles from a variety of manufacturers.\n\n<gallery class=\"center\">\nFile:Peugeot de la Police Nationale. 3e arrondissement de Paris, septembre 2013.JPG|[[Peugeot 308]]\nFile:Renault M\u00e9gane III Police nationale \u00e0 Nice.jpg|[[Renault Megane#M\u00e9gane III (2008\u20132016)|Renault Megane III]]\nFile:Police nationale, gare de Strasbourg f\u00e9vrier 2014.JPG|[[Citro\u00ebn Berlingo#Berlingo / Partner II (2008\u20132018) B9|Citro\u00ebn Berlingo II]]\nFile:Renault Sc\u00e9nic III Police nationale, place de la gare Strasbourg.jpg|[[Renault Sc\u00e9nic#Sc\u00e9nic III (2009\u20132016)|Renault Sc\u00e9nic III]]\nFile:Renault trafic police nationale strasbourg -1.JPG|[[Renault Trafic#Second generation (X83; 2001\u20132014)|Renault Trafic II]]\nFile:Police and gendarmerie-IMG 9236.jpg|Police Motorcycle [[Yamaha FJR1300]]\nFile:Peugeot 308 - Brigade Anti Criminalit\u00e9.jpg|Unmarked anti crime unit ([[Peugeot 308]])\n</gallery>\n\n==Pictures==\n<gallery class=\"center\">\nFile:Police-IMG 4105.jpg|Police in the process of combing.\nFile:CRS (Police fran\u00e7aise).jpg|Police in the process of combing.\n</gallery>\n\n== In popular culture ==\n=== Television series ===\n* ''[[Jules Maigret|Maigret]]'' (various television series)\n* ''The Last Five Minutes'' (''Les cinq derni\u00e8res minutes'') (1958\u20131996)\n* ''Navarro''  (1989\u20132005)\n* ''Commissaire Moulin'' (1976\u20132006)\n* ''Police Judiciaire/P.J.'' (1997\u20132009)\n* ''La Crim<nowiki>'</nowiki>'' (1999\u20132006)\n* ''Commissaire Magellan'' (2009\u2013)\n* ''Les Cordier juge et flic'' (1992\u20132003)\n* ''Commissaire Cordier''  (2004\u20132007)\n* ''Julie Lescaut''  (1991\u20132014)\n* ''Falco'' (2013\u20132016)\n* ''Commissaire Valence'' (2002\u20132008)\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Law enforcement in France]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category multi|Police Nationale|Police of France}}\n* [http://www.davsindia.com/ Official site of the French National Police] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://www.davsindia.com/smart-school-classroom-solution-education-learning-nagpur-pune-mumbai-latur-goa-trivendrum-chennai-bangalore-hyderabad-ahmedabad-surat-indore-jaipur-kolkata-delhi-noida-gurgaon-india-n/ Official site of the French Ministry of Interior] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://www.davsindia.com/virtual-classroom-solutions/ Unofficial site of the National Police] {{in lang|fr}}\n\n{{Law enforcement agencies of France}}\n{{Police}}\n{{Customs}}\n\n[[Category:National Police (France)| ]]\n[[Category:National Central Bureaus of Interpol]]\n[[Category:National law enforcement agencies of France]]\n[[Category:National police forces]]\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=January 2008}}\n{{Infobox Law enforcement agency\n| agencyname        = National Police\n| nativename        = {{lang|fr|Police nationale}}\n| nativenamea       = \n| nativenamer       = \n| commonname        = \n| abbreviation      = \n| patchcaption      = Patch of the National Police\n| logo              = Logo-police-nationale-france.svg \n| logocaption       = \n| badge             = \n| badgecaption      = \n| flag              = \n| flagcaption       = \n| motto = Pro patria vigilant<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gouvernement.fr/gouvernement/police-nationale-une-force-d-action-et-de-protection-au-service-de-tous |title=Police Nationale - Une force d'action et de protection au service de tous |access-date=2013-06-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103084257/http://www.gouvernement.fr/gouvernement/police-nationale-une-force-d-action-et-de-protection-au-service-de-tous |archive-date=2013-11-03 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| mottotranslated   = \n| formedyear        = 1966\n| formedmonthday    = July 9 \n| preceding1        = S\u00fbret\u00e9 nationale (1944\u20131966)\n| employees         = 145,200 (2015)\n| volunteers        = \n| budget            = \n| nongovernment     = \n| country           = France \n| countryabbr       = \n| national          = Yes\n| map               = \n| mapcaption        = \n| sizearea          = 551,695 km\u00b2\n| sizepopulation    = 67.2 million \n| legaljuris        = \n| governingbody     = Cabinet of France\n| governingbodyscnd = \n| constitution1     = \n| police            = Yes\n| local             = Yes\n| overviewtype      = \n| overviewbody      = Direction g\u00e9n\u00e9rale de la police nationale\n| headquarters      = [[Paris]],  [[France]]\n| hqlocmap          = \n| hqlocleft         = \n| hqloctop          = \n| hqlocmappoptitle  = \n| sworntype         = \n| sworn             = \n| unsworntype       = \n| unsworn           = \n| electeetype       = Minister\n| minister1name     = [[Christophe Castaner]] \n| minister1pfo      = [[Minister of the Interior (France)|Ministry of the Interior]]\n| chief1name        = \u00c9ric Morvan \n| chief1position    = Directeur G\u00e9n\u00e9ral de la Police Nationale\n| parentagency      = \n| child1agency      = \n| unittype          = Directorate\n| unitname          = {{collapsible list |title=List of Directorates |[[Direction de l'administration de la police nationale]] |[[Direction de la formation de police nationale]] |[[Direction centrale de la police judiciaire]] |[[Direction centrale de la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 publique]] |[[Direction centrale de la police aux fronti\u00e8res]] |[[Inspection g\u00e9n\u00e9rale de la police nationale]] |[[Direction centrale des compagnies r\u00e9publicaines de s\u00e9curit\u00e9]] |[[Service de coop\u00e9ration technique internationale de police]] |[[Service de protection des hautes personnalit\u00e9s]] |[[Prefecture of Police|Pr\u00e9fecture de police]] |[[Recherche Assistance Intervention Dissuasion]]}}\n| officetype        = \n| officename        = \n| provideragency    = \n| uniformedas       = \n| stationtype       = \n| stations          = \n| airbases          = \n| lockuptype        = \n| lockups           = \n| vehicle1type      = \n| vehicles1         = \n| boat1type         = \n| boats1            = \n| aircraft1type     = Helicopter\n| aircraft1         = 0 see [[S\u00e9curit\u00e9 Civile]]\n| animal1type       = \n| animals1          = \n| person1name       = \n| person1reason     = \n| person1type       = \n| programme1        = \n| activity1name     = \n| activitytype      = \n| anniversary1      = \n| award1            = \n| website           = {{Official website|https://www.police-nationale.interieur.gouv.fr}} {{in lang|fr}}\n| footnotes         = \n| reference         = \n}}\n[[File: General Directorate of the National Police Bastille Day 2013 Paris t111638.jpg |thumb|right|[[Colour guard]] of the General Directorate of the National Police, 2013 [[Bastille Day]] parade, Paris]]\nThe '''National Police''' ({{lang-fr|Police nationale}}), formerly known as the {{lang|fr|[[S\u00fbret\u00e9|S\u00fbret\u00e9 nationale]]}}, is one of two national [[police]] forces, along with the [[National Gendarmerie]], and the main civil law enforcement agency of [[France]], with primary jurisdiction in cities and large towns. The other main agency is the military {{lang|fr|[[French Gendarmerie|Gendarmerie]]}}, with primary jurisdiction in smaller towns and rural and border areas. The National Police comes under the jurisdiction of the [[Minister of the Interior (France)|Ministry of the Interior]] and has about 145,699 employees (in April 2008). Young French citizens can fulfill the [[Civil conscription|mandatory service]] ''[[Service national universel|Service national universel (SNU)]]'' in the police force.<ref>https://www.france24.com/en/20190616-france-trial-macron-new-compulsory-national-service-teen-military</ref><ref>https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-48755605</ref>\n\nThe National Police operates mostly in large cities and towns. In that context:\n\n* it conducts security operations ([[patrol]]s, traffic control, identity checks)\n* under the orders and supervision of the [[investigating magistrate]]s of the judiciary, it conducts criminal enquiries, serves search warrants, etc.; it maintains specific services (\"judicial police\") for criminal enquiries.\n\n== Organization ==\nThe police is commanded by the director-general ({{lang|fr|directeur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral de la police nationale}}) who is currently Jean-Marc Falcone. The director-general is directly in charge of the General Directorate of the National Police ({{lang-fr|Direction G\u00e9n\u00e9rale de la Police nationale}}) (DGPN) and the immediate subordinate of the Minister of the Interior.<ref>[http://www.interieur.gouv.fr/rubriques/c/c3_police_nationale/c33_organisation ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040405062315/http://www.interieur.gouv.fr/rubriques/c/c3_police_nationale/c33_organisation |date=April 5, 2004 }}</ref>\n\nThe police is then sub-divided into (central) directorates which are composed of sub-directorates :\n\n* ''Direction des ressources et des comp\u00e9tences de la police nationale'' (Directorate of Resources and Competences of the National Police; DRCPN):<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.interieur.gouv.fr/sections/a_l_interieur/la_police_nationale/organisation/drcpn |title=Direction des Ressources et des Comp\u00e9tences de la Police Nationale / Organisation - Police nationale - Minist\u00e8re de l'Int\u00e9rieur |language=fr |publisher=Interieur.gouv.fr |date= |accessdate=2013-03-15}}</ref> fusion of the ''Direction de la formation de police nationale'' (Directorate of Training of the National Police; DFPN) and ''Direction de l'administration de la police nationale'' (Directorate of Administration of the National Police; DAPN)\n* ''[[Direction centrale de la Police judiciaire]]'' (Central Directorate of the Judicial Police; DCPJ): charged with all criminal investigations (this mission is fulfilled in the Paris area by the ''[[Direction R\u00e9gionale de Police Judiciaire de Paris]]'' nicknamed after its address \"''36 Quai des Orf\u00e8vres''\", often without the number; the national headquarters of the ''PJ'', as it is usually called in French, are actually located at 11 rue des Saussaies, in the Ministry of the Interior). The main Sub-Directorates of the Judicial Police are: \n** [[Sous-Direction Anti-Terroriste|Sous-direction anti-terroriste]] \"SDAT\" (Anti-Terrorism Sub-Directorate): elite counter-terrorist task-force.\n** [[Sous-Direction de la lutte contre la criminalit\u00e9 organis\u00e9e et la d\u00e9linquance financi\u00e8re]] \"SDLCODP\" (Sub-Directorate for the struggle against organized crime and financial delinquency): It includes all the National Investigation Offices specialized in that field, except the National Itinerant Criminality Struggle Office (managed by the [[Gendarmerie Nationale (France)|Gendarmerie Nationale]])\n** [[Sous-Direction de la police technique et scientifique]] \"SDPTS\" (Sub-directorate of forensics and crime scene investigation)\n** [[Sous-Direction de lutte contre la cybercriminalit\u00e9]] \"SDLC\" (Sub-directorate for the struggle against computer and internet crime)\n* ''[[Central Directorate of Public Security|Direction centrale de la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 publique]]'' (Central Directorate of Public Security; DCSP): patrol and response, misdemeanour investigations, emergency help; approximatively 80% of the workforce.\n**[[Groupes d'Intervention de la Police Nationale]] (Intervention Groups of the National Police; GIPN): Nine regional SWAT teams.\n* ''[[Direction centrale de la police aux fronti\u00e8res]]'' (Central Directorate of Border Police; DCPAF): performs identity checks with \"[[Directorate-General of Customs and Indirect Taxes|La douane fran\u00e7aise]]\" (official name: [[Direction g\u00e9n\u00e9rale des Douanes et Droits Indirects]]) and handles illegal immigration.\n* ''Inspection g\u00e9n\u00e9rale de la police nationale'' (General Inspectorate of the National Police, IGPN): headed by the [[Inspector General]] and responsible for [[Internal affairs (law enforcement)|internal affairs]]. In the Paris Area, these tasks are assigned to a dedicated service\u2014the ''Inspection G\u00e9n\u00e9rale des Services'' (General Inspectorate of the Services).\n* ''[[Compagnies R\u00e9publicaines de S\u00e9curit\u00e9|Direction centrale des compagnies r\u00e9publicaines de s\u00e9curit\u00e9]]'' (Central Directorate of the Republican Security Companies; DCCRS): [[riot police]], [[motorway police]], and [[mountain rescue]]; commonly referred to as the CRS.\n* ''Service de coop\u00e9ration technique internationale de police'' (Technical International Police Co-operation Service; SCTIP).\n* ''[[Service de protection des hautes personnalit\u00e9s]]'' (Important Persons Protection Service; SPHP): VIP protection such as foreign diplomats and also responsible for the protection of the [[President of the French Republic]] through the  '[[Groupe de S\u00e9curit\u00e9 de la Pr\u00e9sidence de la R\u00e9publique]]'.\n* The ''Unit\u00e9 de Coordination de la Lutte Antiterroriste'' (UCLAT; Counterterrorism Struggle Coordination Unit) and its [[Recherche Assistance Intervention Dissuasion]] (Research, Assistance, Intervention, Deterrence; RAID) unit.\n\nThe ''Pr\u00e9fet de Police'', currently [[Bernard Boucault]], under direct orders of the Minister of the Interior, manages the ''[[Paris Police|Pr\u00e9fecture de Police de Paris]]'' which includes all police and security services in [[Paris]] and neighbouring d\u00e9partements, those services not being under the control of the director-general. The police forces in the other d\u00e9partements of the [[\u00cele-de-France (region)|\u00cele-de-France]] region are under the direct command of the [[Pr\u00e9fet de d\u00e9partement|Pr\u00e9fet]] (D\u00e9partement Prefect) in charge, being himself under the supervision of the ''Pr\u00e9fet de Police'' as far as the active on-the-field police work is concerned, and under the control of the director-general for the rest.\n\n=== Former directorates ===\nAs of 1 July 2008, the following two National Police directorates:\n* ''[[Direction de la surveillance du territoire]]'' (Directorate of Territorial Surveillance; DST) \u2013 [[counter-intelligence]], [[counterespionage]], [[counterterrorism]]\n* ''[[Renseignements g\u00e9n\u00e9raux|Direction centrale des renseignements g\u00e9n\u00e9raux]]'' (Central Directorate of General Information; DCRG or RG) \u2013 police intelligence, records, research, analysis (and also policing [[gambling]] and [[horse racing]], two activities which are now in the hands of the \"Service central des courses et jeux\" SCCJ, a unit of the Judicial Police)\nwere merged into one single domestic [[intelligence agency]] titled the ''[[Direction centrale du renseignement int\u00e9rieur]]'' (DCRI). The DCRI was placed directly under the [[Minister of the Interior (France)|Ministry of the Interior]].<ref>[http://www.interieur.gouv.fr/sections/a_la_une/toute_l_actualite/securite-interieure/creation-dcri Official announcement of the DCRI's launch on the website of the French Ministry of the Interior.]</ref>\n\n== Ranks ==\nThe National Police is divided into three ''corps'', in the terminology of the [[French Civil Service]], in ascending order of seniority:\n* The ''Corps d'encadrement et d'application'' (Management and Enforcement Corps) corresponds approximately to the enlisted and [[non-commissioned officer|non-commissioned]] ranks in a military force, or to [[constable]]s and [[sergeant]]s in a [[British police|British]]-style civil police force.\n<gallery class=\"center\">\nFile:Police nationale-gardien de la paix stagiaire.svg|''Gardien de la paix stagiaire'' (keeper of the peace, intern\") 1st year after school.\nFile:Police nationale-gardien de la paix.svg|''Gardien de la paix'' (keeper of the peace)\nFile:Police nationale-Brigadier.svg|''Brigadier''\nFile:Police nationale-Brigadier chef.svg|''Brigadier-chef''\nFile:Police nationale-Brigadier major.svg|''Major''\n</gallery>\n\n* The ''Corps de commandement'' (Command Corps) corresponds approximately to the lower [[commissioned officer|commissioned]] ranks of a military force, or the grades of [[inspector]] and [[chief inspector]] in a British-style civil police force. These ranks were previously known as ''inspecteurs'' if detectives or ''officiers de la paix'' if uniformed, although [[Compagnies R\u00e9publicaines de S\u00e9curit\u00e9|CRS]] officers always used the current ranks.\n<gallery class=\"center\">\nFile:Police nationale-\u00e9l\u00e8ve lieutenant de police.svg|''Lieutenant student''\nFile:Police nationale-lieutenant stagiaire.svg|''Lieutenant intern''\nFile:Police nationale-lieutenant.svg|''[[Lieutenant#Police_rank|Lieutenant]]'' (formerly ''Officier de la paix'' or ''Inspecteur'')\nFile:Police nationale-capitaine.svg|''[[Police captain|Capitaine]]'' (formerly ''Officer de la paix principal'' or ''Inspecteur principal'')\nFile:Police nationale-commandant.svg|''[[Commandant]]'' (formerly ''Commandant'' or ''Inspecteur divisionnaire'')\nFile:Police nationale-commandant.svg|''[[Commandant]] divisionnaire''<br> <small>Same insignia as Commandant but with gold oak leaf</small>\nFile:Police nationale-commandant.svg|''[[Commandant]] divisionnaire functionnel''<br> <small>Same insignia as Commandant but with silver oak leaf</small>\n</gallery>\n\n\n\n* The ''Corps de conception et de direction'' (Conception and Direction Corps) corresponds approximately to the higher commissioned ranks of a military force, or to grades of [[Chief Superintendent (police)|Chief superintendent]] and chief officers in a British-style civil police force.\n<gallery class=\"center\">\nFile:Police nationale-commissaire.svg|''[[Commissaire de police]]'' (Chief superintendent)\nFile:Police nationale-commissaire divisionnaire.svg|''[[Commissaire divisionnaire]]'' (Ass. Chief Constable)\nFile:Police nationale-contr\u00f4leur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral.svg|''Contr\u00f4leur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral'' (Controller General) the equivalent of a D.A.C. or Assistant commissioner. In the 'provincial constabularies', this is the rank of an Chief Constable.\nFile:Police nationale-inspecteur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral.svg|''Inspecteur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral'' ([[Inspector General]]) This is the equivalent of a Deputy Commissioner in Metropolitan Police of London.\nFile:Police nationale-directeur des services actifs.svg|''Directeur des services actifs'' (Director of the Active Services) Equivalent of a Commissioner in London in a British-style police force\n</gallery>\n\nAll the ranks insignia may be worn either on the shoulders or on the chest. In the latter they are square-shaped.\n\nPrior to 1995 two civilian corps (\"Inspecteurs\" and \"Enqu\u00eateurs\") existed in which plainclothes officers were given the training and authority to conduct investigations. The closest American equivalent is the [[detective]].\n\n== Equipment ==\n\n=== Weapons ===\n[[File:DCB-Shooting SIG-SAUER 2022.jpg|thumb|[[SIG Pro|SP 2022]], the present standard issued sidearm of French police officers.]]\n\nIn 1935, the French police used a variety of side arms, both revolvers and semi-automatic pistols, notably comprising the [[MAS 1873 revolver|MAS 1873]], the [[Mod\u00e8le 1892 revolver|MAS 1892]], the [[FN M1900]], [[Ruby pistol]]s, and a variety of privately purchased weapons.\n\nImmediately after the [[Second World War]], a variety of military side arms was used, often captured weapons provided by the Army or French-produced German-designed weapons, such as the [[Mauser HSc]] or the [[Walther P38]] for sidearms, and the [[Karabiner 98k]] rifle.\n\nIn 1951, a standardisation was performed on the [[RR 51]] pistol<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.littlegun.info/arme%20francaise/artisans%20m%20n%20o/a%20mapf%20mod%20r%20gb.htm |title=Nouvelle page 0 |publisher=Littlegun.info |date= |accessdate=2013-03-15}}</ref> in [[7.65\u00d717mm]] and on the [[MAS-38]] and [[MAT-49]] for submachine guns. From 1953, in the context of heightening violence of the [[Algeria War]], CRS units were upgraded to the [[9\u00d719mm]] [[MAC Mle 1950]].\n\nIn the early 1960s, large-caliber revolvers were introduced, culminating with the introduction of the [[Manurhin MR 73]] and the [[Ruger SP101]]. In the 80s, a process to standardize revolvers was initiated. The 1970s also saw the introduction of assault rifles{{clarify|date=January 2015}} (such as the [[SIG SG 543]]) to fend off heavily armed organised crime and terrorism.\n\nIn the 2000s, the police started switching to semi-automatic pistols and to the [[9\u00d719mm Parabellum]] cartridge. For some years, the standard sidearm in the National Police and the [[Gendarmerie Nationale (France)|Gendarmerie Nationale]] was the [[Beretta 92|PAMAS G1]], which was French licensed and made. In 2003 both agencies made the biggest small arms contract since the Second World War<ref name=\"Ayoob\">Ayoob, Massad F.: ''The Gun Digest Book of SIG-Sauer: A Complete Look at SIG-Sauer Pistols'', page 80. Gun Digest, 2004.</ref> for about 250,000 [[SIG Pro|SIG Sauer Pro SP 2022s]], a custom-tailored variant of the SIG Pro, replacing the PAMAS-G1 and several other pistols in service. The weapons are planned to stay in service until the year 2022, hence the weapon name. It is possible the pistols will be used past 2022 as the agency purchased more pistols in late 2018 possibly indicating the pistols may be used beyond 2022. <ref>\nhttps://www.thefirearmblog.com/blog/2018/12/05/sig-sp2022-for-french-police/</ref>\n\n\nFor greater threats the police use slightly modified [[Ruger Mini-14]]s purchased in the 1970s.\n\nSome sources have claimed the use of the [[Spectre M4]] by the French National Police.\n\n=== Cars ===\nWhile the vast majority of vehicles are screen printed French brand (mainly Renault, Citro\u00ebn and Peugeot), some service vehicles are provided by Ford and Opel. Plainclothes officers or specialised branches use vehicles from a variety of manufacturers.\n\n<gallery class=\"center\">\nFile:Peugeot de la Police Nationale. 3e arrondissement de Paris, septembre 2013.JPG|[[Peugeot 308]]\nFile:Renault M\u00e9gane III Police nationale \u00e0 Nice.jpg|[[Renault Megane#M\u00e9gane III (2008\u20132016)|Renault Megane III]]\nFile:Police nationale, gare de Strasbourg f\u00e9vrier 2014.JPG|[[Citro\u00ebn Berlingo#Berlingo / Partner II (2008\u20132018) B9|Citro\u00ebn Berlingo II]]\nFile:Renault Sc\u00e9nic III Police nationale, place de la gare Strasbourg.jpg|[[Renault Sc\u00e9nic#Sc\u00e9nic III (2009\u20132016)|Renault Sc\u00e9nic III]]\nFile:Renault trafic police nationale strasbourg -1.JPG|[[Renault Trafic#Second generation (X83; 2001\u20132014)|Renault Trafic II]]\nFile:Police and gendarmerie-IMG 9236.jpg|Police Motorcycle [[Yamaha FJR1300]]\nFile:Peugeot 308 - Brigade Anti Criminalit\u00e9.jpg|Unmarked anti crime unit ([[Peugeot 308]])\n</gallery>\n\n==Pictures==\n<gallery class=\"center\">\nFile:Police-IMG 4105.jpg|Police in the process of combing.\nFile:CRS (Police fran\u00e7aise).jpg|Police in the process of combing.\n</gallery>\n\n== In popular culture ==\n=== Television series ===\n* ''[[Jules Maigret|Maigret]]'' (various television series)\n* ''The Last Five Minutes'' (''Les cinq derni\u00e8res minutes'') (1958\u20131996)\n* ''Navarro''  (1989\u20132005)\n* ''Commissaire Moulin'' (1976\u20132006)\n* ''Police Judiciaire/P.J.'' (1997\u20132009)\n* ''La Crim<nowiki>'</nowiki>'' (1999\u20132006)\n* ''Commissaire Magellan'' (2009\u2013)\n* ''Les Cordier juge et flic'' (1992\u20132003)\n* ''Commissaire Cordier''  (2004\u20132007)\n* ''Julie Lescaut''  (1991\u20132014)\n* ''Falco'' (2013\u20132016)\n* ''Commissaire Valence'' (2002\u20132008)\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Law enforcement in France]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category multi|Police Nationale|Police of France}}\n* [http://www.police-nationale.interieur.gouv.fr Official site of the French National Police] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://www.interieur.gouv.fr/ Official site of the French Ministry of Interior] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://www.concourspolice.fr Unofficial site of the National Police] {{in lang|fr}}\n\n{{Law enforcement agencies of France}}\n{{Police}}\n{{Customs}}\n\n[[Category:National Police (France)| ]]\n[[Category:National Central Bureaus of Interpol]]\n[[Category:National law enforcement agencies of France]]\n[[Category:National police forces]]\n", "name_user": "Bhushan.ngp", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Police_(France)"}
{"title_page": "Boss Engira Bhaskaran", "text_new": "{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Boss Engira Bhaskaran\n| image          = Boss Engira Bhaskaran.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n\n| director       = [[M. Rajesh (director)|M. Rajesh]]\n| producer       = [[Arya (actor)|Arya]] <br />  K. S. Sreenivasan\n| writer         = M. Rajesh\n| starring       = [[Arya (actor)|Arya]]<br />[[Nayantara]]<br />[[Santhanam (actor)|Santhanam]]\n| music          = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cinematography = [[Sakthi Saravanan]]\n| editing        = [[Vivek Harshan]]\n| studio         = Vasan Visual Ventures\n| distributor    = [[Udhayanidhi Stalin|Red Giant Movies]]<br />[[The Show People]]<br />[[Ayngaran International]]\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2010|9|10}}\n| runtime        = 161 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = \u20b918 crore<ref name=\"bestoftheyear.in\">https://bestoftheyear.in/movie/boss-engira-bhaskaran/</ref>\n| gross          = \u20b930 crore<ref name=\"bestoftheyear.in\">https://bestoftheyear.in/movie/boss-engira-bhaskaran/</ref>\n}}\n'''''Boss Engira Bhaskaran''''' ({{lit|Boss alias Bhaskaran}}) is a 2010 Tamil [[Romance film|romantic]] [[comedy film]] written and directed by [[M. Rajesh (director)|M. Rajesh]] who earlier directed ''[[Siva Manasula Sakthi]]'' (2009). Starring [[Arya (actor)|Arya]], [[Nayantara]] and [[Santhanam (actor)|Santhanam]] in lead roles, the film is produced by K. S. Sreenivasan and features music scored by [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] and cinematography handled by [[Sakthi Saravanan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/50850.html|title=Arya is Boss aka Baskaran|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=21 October 2009}}</ref>\n\nThe film revolves around a young happy-go-lucky man, Bhaskaran, who is unemployed and lives an easygoing life, neglecting his career and future. When he meets a young girl, Chandrika, in whom he falls in love, he is bound to change his lifestyle, in order to marry her eventually.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-10-21/news-interviews/28090954_1_malayalam-film-arya-tamil-film|title=Boss, Nayan\u2019s back in Tamil!|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=21 October 2009|date=21 October 2009}}</ref> The film released on 10 September 2010 to highly positive reviews and also became commercially successful.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/arya-scores-a-century-news-tamil-kmrtuTgeefd.html |title=Arya scores a century|publisher=Sify |date=19 December 2010 |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe film was remade in Kannada as ''[[Parijatha]]'' (2011)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bangaloremirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/reviews/parijata-akshay-kumars-mein-khiladi/articleshow/21427153.cms|title=Parijata : Akshay Kumar's Mein Khiladi|website=Bangalore Mirror|access-date=2018-06-15}}</ref> and in Bengali as ''[[Raja Rani Raji]]'' (2018).\n\n== Plot ==\nBhaskaran is a happy-go-lucky youth who is yet to complete his [[Bachelor of Arts|B. A. Degree]], writing [[Arrears|arrear]] examinations for years. His only friend, Nallathambi, owns a barber hair saloon shop, which he received as dowry for marrying a woman who was two months pregnant. Bhaskaran, during an arrear exam, happens to meet  Chandrika, a lecturer, and instantly gets attracted to her, though she disapproves of him because he attempted to [[Academic dishonesty|copy]] during the exam.\n\nBhaskaran lives with his widowed mother, Sivakami, his older brother Saravanan (a veterinarian) and his younger sister Nithya, who is a college student wanting to become a TV compere. When Saravanan falls in love and marries Nandhini, Bhaskaran discovers that Nandhini's younger sister is Chandrika, and wishes to marry her. When he approaches his family for the alliance, his unemployment is repeatedly mentioned, rankling him, so he leaves his house to prove himself.\n\nBhaskaran faces many obstacles in his path to prove himself. He is insulted by Chandrika's father, Shanmugasundaram, and does not even have a place to live. After many difficulties, Bhaskaran, with the support of Nallathambi, establishes a tutorial for [[tenth grade|Class X]] students. Nallathambi goes and gets money from Velpandi, a local don, who signs an agreement that if his son Paalpandi does not pass in his exam, he will take Nallathambi's property and make him work in his cow dung place.\n\nVelpandi reveals his family history: his father, in his Class X examination, forced his teacher to write the exam. Velpandi, during his exam, wrote only four words in his paper with a [[billhook]] symbol, blackmailing the teacher into making him pass or risk being killed. Velpandi's son Paalpandi sleeps in the exam hall and if anybody tries to wake him, he will bite the teacher's hand.\n\nHowever, in the end, Paalpandi starts to study and makes others listen in the class when Bhaskaran appoints a blind teacher. Despite early setbacks, Bhaskaran makes a very heavy profit on the deal, while his students top in the state and Paalpandi passes in his exam with good marks. Velpandi tears the agreement, offers Nallathambi a huge amount of money with no interest and appreciates him for making Paalpandi pass in the exams.\n\nIt also convinces Chandrika, who eventually reciprocates his love. However, Shanmugasundaram is against the marriage as he had once been insulted by a drunk Nallathambi as revenge for not having sanctioned a loan to Bhaskaran. Shiva, a supposed [[teetotalism|teetotaller]] and the son of a businessman who is Shanmugasundram's friend, is introduced as Chandrika's prospective groom. Bhaskaran then confronts Shiva, revealing to him that he loves Chandrika. The two get into a fight soon after, but when Shanmugasundaram arrives at the spot, he learns the truth: Shiva and Bhaskaran are now friends and the whole fight was just a drama set by Nallathambi, Shiva supports their marriage. Under Shiva and Bhaskaran's orders, a disappointed Shanmugasundaram is forced to unite Bhaskaran and Chandrika. In the end, it is revealed that the director called Shiva and told him to stop fighting and unite Bhaskaran and Chandrika.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Arya (actor)|Arya]] as Bhaskaran\n* [[Nayantara]] as Chandrika\n* [[Santhanam (actor)|Santhanam]] as \"Thala Thalapathy\" Nallathambi\n* [[Subbu Panchu Arunachalam|Subbu Panchu]] as Saravanan\n* [[Chitra Lakshmanan]] as Shanmugasundaram/mongoose mandaiya\n* [[Rajendran]] as Velpandi\n* [[Ashvin Raja]] as Paalpandi\n* [[Vijayalakshmi (Kannada actress)|Vijaylakshmi]] as Nandhini Saravanan\n* [[Lakshmi Ramakrishnan]] as Sivakami\n* [[Swaminathan]] as Matured Student\n* Monisha  as Nithya\n* [[Poorni]] as Annapoorani\n* [[Jiiva]] in a [[guest appearance]] as [[Siva Manasula Sakthi|Shiva]]\n* [[Shakeela]] as in a guest appearance as Parimala\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\nThe film was officially launched on 19 November 2009 at the [[AVM Studios]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/gallery/Events/20146.html |title=Events \u2013 'Boss Engira Baskaran' Movie Launch |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=19 November 2009 |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> with the film starting shooting in December first week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/fullstory.php?id=14920455 |title=Arya\u2019s Boss Engira Bhaskaran launched!|publisher=Sify |date=20 November 2009 |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> Rajesh, following his [[sleeper hit]] ''[[Siva Manasula Sakthi]]'', decided to make another comedy film and to cast [[Arya (actor)|Arya]], who appeared in a cameo role in ''Siva Manasula Sakthi'', in the titular role,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/50850.html |title=Arya is Boss aka Baskaran \u2013 Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> while [[Jiiva]] in return would make a cameo appearance in the film.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.southdreamz.com/2010/04/jeevas-reciprocations-for-boss.html |title=Jeeva's reciprocations for 'Boss' |publisher=Southdreamz.com |date=10 April 2010 |accessdate=4 August 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111009183456/http://www.southdreamz.com/2010/04/jeevas-reciprocations-for-boss.html |archive-date=9 October 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> As the film's backdrop is set to be both village as well as city, the film was shot at various location including [[Thanjavur]], [[Mysore]] and [[Tiruchirappalli|Trichy]].<ref name=shoot>{{cite news|last=V Lakshmi|title=Director Rajesh gets talking to Whatt\u2019\u2019s Hot on his upcoming project Boss Engira Baskaran.....|url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Archive&Source=Page&Skin=TOINEW&BaseHref=TOICH%2F2010%2F08%2F06&ViewMode=GIF&PageLabel=30&EntityId=Ar03002&AppName=1|accessdate=12 March 2014|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]}}</ref> A major part of the film was filmed at [[Kumbakonam]], while a few scenes were shot in [[Chennai]] as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/52594.html |title=Nayantara is with \u2018Boss Engira Baskaran\u2019! - Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/jan-10-01/nayanthara-boss-engira-baskaran-08-01-10.html |title=Nayan moves to Chennai |publisher=Behindwoods |date=8 January 2010 |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> Shooting was also carried on in the [[Swiss Alps]], where some song sequences were picturized.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14946085 |title=Arya & Nayan goes to Swiss Alps|publisher=Sify |date=21 June 2010 |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://chennaionline.com/movies/preview/Aarya-and-Nayantara-to-romance-in-Switzerland/20103925013912.col |title=Aarya and Nayantara to romance in Switzerland &#124; preview \u2013 Movies |publisher=ChennaiOnline |date=25 June 2010 |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> Principal photography ended on 3 August 2010 with the completion of the last song that was canned at a set erected at [[Buckingham and Carnatic Mills|Binny Mills]] near [[Chennai]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14952026 |title=Boss Engira Bhaskaran shoot is complete|publisher=Sify |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> Arya revealed that the script went through changes during production, with Rajesh eventually opting not to include portions where Bhaskaran's brother gets killed in the film. Instead of implementing a revenge script, Rajesh chose to make it a full-length comedy.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xjzbu0-et-0</ref>\n\nWhile Vasan Visual Ventures that produced Arya's ''[[Naan Kadavul]]'', produced this film as well, Arya purchased the rights in the midst to release it under his own production banner \"The Show People\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/58265.html |title=Arya buys over \u2018Boss Engira Baskaran\u2019 - Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> The film's distribution rights, however, were again acquired by Red Giant Movies, led by [[Udhayanidhi Stalin]], who would enact the lead role in Rajesh's next project.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/58980.html |title=Red Giant acquires Boss Engira Bhaskaran \u2013 Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Boss Engira Bhaskaran\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 27 August 2010\n| recorded   = 2009\u20132010\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 23:03\n| label      = [[Think Music India|Think Music]]\n| producer   = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| prev_title = [[Naan Mahaan Alla (2010 film)|Naan Mahaan Alla]]\n| prev_year  = 2010\n| next_title = [[Pathinaaru]]\n| next_year  = 2010\n}}\n\nFollowing the success of ''[[Siva Manasula Sakthi]]'', [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] composed the musical score and soundtrack of ''Boss Engira Bhaskaran'', too.<ref name=\"indiaglitz1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/55770.html |title=\u2018Boss\u2019 gets ready \u2013 Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> The soundtrack album, which was released on 27 August 2010 at Sathyam Cinemas,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14954826 |title=Suriya launches Boss Engira Baskaran audio|publisher=Sify |date=28 August 2010 |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref> contains 5 tracks, featuring lyrics penned by [[Na. Muthukumar]]. The soundtrack received positive response.\n\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Tracklist\n| extra_column    = Singer(s)\n| total_length    = 23:03\n| title1          = Ada Boss Boss\n| extra1          = [[Sathyan (singer)|Sathyan]]\n| length1         = 3:58\n| title2          = Yaar Intha Penthan\n| extra2          = [[Haricharan (singer)|Haricharan]]\n| length2         = 5:01\n| title3          = Thathi Thaavum Paper Naan\n| extra3          = [[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]]\n| length3         = 4:44\n| title4          = Iyley Iyley\n| extra4          = [[Vijay Prakash]]\n| length4         = 5:04\n| title5          = Mama Mama\n| extra5          = Vijay Yesudas, [[Shweta Mohan]]\n| length5         = 4:16\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe satellite rights of the film were secured by [[Kalaignar TV|Kalaignar]]. The film was given a \"U\" certificate by the [[Indian Censor Board]]. In November 2011, it was shown at the International Tamil Film Festival held in Uglich, Russia, alongside ''[[Thillana Mohanambal]]'' (1968), ''[[Chandramukhi]]'' (2005), ''[[Sivaji (film)|Sivaji]]'' (2007), ''[[Angadi Theru]]'' (2010), ''[[Thenmerku Paruvakaatru]]'' (2010) and ''[[Ko (film)|Ko]]'' (2011).<ref>http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/taste-of-sivaji-magic-for-russian-film-buffs/article2513543.ece</ref>  The film was eventually dubbed into [[Telugu language|Telugu]] as ''Nene Ambani'' which released on 17 December 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.sulekha.com/nene-ambani_telugu_movie_release-date |title=Nene Ambani Release Date&#124;Nene Ambani Telugu Movie Releasing Date&#124;Arya&#124;Nayantara&#124;Santhanam&#124; |publisher=Movies.sulekha.com |date=17 December 2010 |accessdate=8 November 2012}}</ref>\n\n=== Box office ===\n''Boss Engira Bhaskaran'' sold 7.3 million tickets worldwide. It released on [[Eid ul-Fitr|Eid]] day, the end of [[Ramadan]], opening across 240 screens in [[Tamil Nadu]] with reportedly 95.5% average theatre occupancy, which, according to trade sources, was the best ever first day opening for Arya then,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14956576 |title=Boss Engira Baskaran- Super Opening|publisher=Sify |date=13 September 2010 |accessdate=8 November 2012}}</ref> which resulted in an increase of the number of shows and screens.<ref name=\"240screens\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-09-13/news-interviews/28235592_1_screens-release-tamil-film|title=A big fat K\u2019wood opening|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=13 September 2010|accessdate=15 September 2010|first1=Sreedhar|last1=Pillai}}</ref><ref name=\"sify.com\">{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14956894&cid=13525926 |title=Chennai box office (Sep 10 \u2013 12)|publisher=Sify |date=15 September 2010 |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref> In its opening weekend, the film was said to have earned {{INR}}58 lakh in [[Chennai]], as reported by Behindwoods,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-slide-shows/movie-4/top-ten-movies-sep-13/tamil-cinema-topten-movie-boss-engira-baskaran.html |title=Boss Engira Baskaran |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref> while according to [[Sify]].com, it grossed {{INR}}65 lakh.<ref name=\"sify.com\" /> At the end of the second weekend, the film had netted {{INR}}10 crore from 275 screens.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14957364&cid=13525926 |title=Chennai Box-office (Sep 17-19)|publisher=Sify |date=22 September 2010 |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref>\n\n=== Critical response ===\nBoss Engira Bhaskaran received positive reviews upon release. ''[[Sify]]'' stated that \"Rajesh has pulled off the impossible, making a family comedy work a second time armed with nothing more than a few situational gaffes and couple of funny dialogues. It\u2019s pure escapist fare and will work big time, as there is paucity of healthy entertainment for the family audiences.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/boss-engira-bhaskaran-review-tamil-14956349.html |title=Movie Review:Boss Engira Bhaskaran|publisher=Sify |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref> ''Indiaglitz'' wrote \"Rajesh has made spoof of some contemporary Tamil films in an enjoyable manner.\" and \"''Boss Engira Baskaran'' is right there oozing with abundant energy and unlimited fun. Kudos to Udhayanidhi for choosing quality films with varied stories that leave an impression with the masses.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/review/11695.html |title=Boss Engira Baskaran Tamil Movie Review |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=10 September 2010 |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref> ''Chennai Online'' specially pointed out the plus points of the film \"The comic scenes aided by dialogues and the bonding between the two friends are a huge plus and reason enough to see the movie. The casting of each character has been aptly done with no room for excess anywhere making for one smooth ride all through. Nayan and Arya make an adequate pair though there are no great sparks of chemistry between them. However Nayan does make a pretty picture throughout.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chennaionline.com/movies/movie-reviews/20105310055327/Movie-Review-Boss-Engira-Baskaran.col |title=Movie Review: 'Boss Engira Baskaran' &#124; Movie Review \u2013 Movies |publisher=ChennaiOnline |date=10 September 2010 |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref>\n\n''Behindwoods'' gave 2.5 out of 5 and expressed that \"Director Rajesh might just pull it off this time too because he\u2019s got everything right for a comic caper. He also efficiently camouflages the saggy little portions in both the halves of his movie with crisply written dialogues. Perfect for a weekend in which you decide not to give your brain much work.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-2/boss-engira-baskaran-movie-review.html |title=Boss Engira Baskaran Movie Review \u2013 Tamil Movie Boss Engira Baskaran Movie Review |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref> A critic from the ''[[Times of India]]'' gave 3 out of 5 and praised the film saying \"When the director shows Boss watching 'Annamalai' on TV and getting inspired, you are not surprised. But his excuses, when facing various career options, make Boss an original. The tutorial college angle may be predictable, but soon humour is back on track, and it is enjoyable. You will also come away with some amazing performances.\"<ref>{{cite news| url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/movie-reviews/Boss-Engira-Bhaskaran/movie-review/6547029.cms | work=The Times of India | title=Boss Engira Bhaskaran | date=10 September 2010}}</ref>\n\n=== Awards ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year!! Award !! Category!! Character !! Cast\n|-\n| 2011 || [[Vijay Awards]] || Best Comedian  || Nallathambi || Santhanam\n|}\n\n== Legacy ==\nThe dialogue \"Nanbenda\" spoken by Santhanam in the film became famous and went viral after the release. The dialogue has inspired a film of [[Nannbenda|same name]]. \"The title, which means friend, was apt because it's a story about two friends. So we felt it will make sense to use it,\" the film's director Jagadish said. Jagadish is the former associate of filmmaker Rajesh.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/regional/south-follows-bollywood-popular-dialogues-songs-inspire-film-titles/article1-1281682.aspx |title=South follows Bollywood: Popular dialogues, songs inspire film titles |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=2014-12-28 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141112182610/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/regional/south-follows-bollywood-popular-dialogues-songs-inspire-film-titles/article1-1281682.aspx |archivedate=12 November 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Another term used by Santhanam in the film, \"Appatakkar\" ([[Know-it-all|know-all]]) also gained popularity.<ref>http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Therikavidalama-to-Senjiduven-Quirky-Kwood-dialogues/articleshow/49337190.cms</ref><ref>http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/Tamil-is-semma-gethu-language-machi/articleshow/50884605.cms</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|3}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|1606183}}\n\n{{M. Rajesh}}\n{{The Show People}}\n\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Tiruchirappalli]]\n[[Category:2010s romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n[[Category:Tamil films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Films directed by M. Rajesh]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Boss Engira Bhaskaran\n| image          = Boss Engira Bhaskaran.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n\n| director       = [[M. Rajesh (director)|M. Rajesh]]\n| producer       = [[Arya (actor)|Arya]] <br />  K. S. Sreenivasan\n| writer         = M. Rajesh\n| starring       = [[Arya (actor)|Arya]]<br />[[Nayantara]]<br />[[Santhanam (actor)|Santhanam]]\n| music          = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cinematography = [[Sakthi Saravanan]]\n| editing        = [[Vivek Harshan]]\n| studio         = Vasan Visual Ventures\n| distributor    = [[Udhayanidhi Stalin|Red Giant Movies]]<br />[[The Show People]]<br />[[Ayngaran International]]\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2010|9|10}}\n| runtime        = 161 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = \u20b918 crore<ref name=\"bestoftheyear.in\">https://bestoftheyear.in/movie/boss-engira-bhaskaran/</ref>\n| gross          = \u20b930 crore<ref name=\"bestoftheyear.in\">https://bestoftheyear.in/movie/boss-engira-bhaskaran/</ref>\n}}\n'''''Boss Engira Bhaskaran''''' ({{lit|Boss alias Bhaskaran}}) is a 2010 Tamil [[Romance film|romantic]] [[comedy film]] written and directed by [[M. Rajesh (director)|M. Rajesh]] who earlier directed ''[[Siva Manasula Sakthi]]'' (2009). Starring [[Arya (actor)|Arya]], [[Nayantara]] and [[Santhanam (actor)|Santhanam]] in lead roles, the film is produced by K. S. Sreenivasan and features music scored by [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] and cinematography handled by [[Sakthi Saravanan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/50850.html|title=Arya is Boss aka Baskaran|publisher=IndiaGlitz|accessdate=21 October 2009}}</ref>\n\nThe film revolves around a young happy-go-lucky man, Bhaskaran, who is unemployed and lives an easygoing life, neglecting his career and future. When he meets a young girl, Chandrika, in whom he falls in love, he is bound to change his lifestyle, in order to marry her eventually.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-10-21/news-interviews/28090954_1_malayalam-film-arya-tamil-film|title=Boss, Nayan\u2019s back in Tamil!|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=21 October 2009|date=21 October 2009}}</ref> The film released on 10 September 2010 to highly positive reviews and also became commercially successful.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/arya-scores-a-century-news-tamil-kmrtuTgeefd.html |title=Arya scores a century|publisher=Sify |date=19 December 2010 |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe film was remade in Kannada as ''[[Parijatha]]'' (2011)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bangaloremirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/reviews/parijata-akshay-kumars-mein-khiladi/articleshow/21427153.cms|title=Parijata : Akshay Kumar's Mein Khiladi|website=Bangalore Mirror|access-date=2018-06-15}}</ref> and in Bengali as ''[[Raja Rani Raji]]'' (2018).\n\n== Plot ==\nBhaskaran is a happy-go-lucky youth who is yet to complete his [[Bachelor of Arts|B. A. Degree]], writing [[Arrears|arrear]] examinations for years. His only friend, Nallathambi, owns a barber hair saloon shop, which he received as dowry for marrying a woman who was two months pregnant. Bhaskaran, during an arrear exam, happens to meet  Chandrika, a lecturer, and instantly gets attracted to her, though she disapproves of him because he attempted to [[Academic dishonesty|copy]] during the exam.\n\nBhaskaran lives with his widowed mother, Sivakami, his older brother Saravanan (a veterinarian) and his younger sister Nithya, who is a college student wanting to become a TV compere. When Saravanan falls in love and gets married to a woman named Nandhini, Bhaskaran discovers that Nandhini's younger sister is Chandrika, and wishes to marry her. When he approaches his family for the alliance, everyone talks of his unemployed status which rankles him and causes him to leave his house to prove himself.\n\nBhaskaran faces many obstacles in his path to prove himself. He is insulted by Chandrika's father, Shanmugasundaram, and does not even have a place to live. After many difficulties, Bhaskaran, with the support of Nallathambi, establishes a tutorial for [[tenth grade|Class X]] students. Nallathambi goes and gets money from Velpandi, a local don, who signs an agreement that if his son Paalpandi does not pass in his exam, he will take Nallathambi's property and make him work in his cow dung place.\n\nVelpandi reveals his family history: his father, in his Class X examination, forced his teacher to write the exam. Velpandi, during his exam, wrote only four words in his paper with a [[billhook]] symbol, blackmailing the teacher into making him pass or risk being killed. Velpandi's son Paalpandi sleeps in the exam hall and if anybody tries to wake him, he will bite the teacher's hand.\n\nHowever, in the end, Paalpandi starts to study and makes others listen in the class when Bhaskaran appoints a blind teacher. Despite early setbacks, Bhaskaran makes a very heavy profit on the deal, while his students top in the state and Paalpandi passes in his exam with good marks. Velpandi tears the agreement, offers Nallathambi a huge amount of money with no interest and appreciates him for making Paalpandi pass in the exams.\n\nIt also convinces Chandrika, who eventually reciprocates his love. However, Shanmugasundaram is against the marriage as he had once been insulted by a drunk Nallathambi as revenge for not having sanctioned a loan to Bhaskaran. Shiva, a supposed [[teetotalism|teetotaller]] and the son of a businessman who is Shanmugasundram's friend, is introduced as Chandrika's prospective groom. Bhaskaran then confronts Shiva, revealing to him that he loves Chandrika. The two get into a fight soon after, but when Shanmugasundaram arrives at the spot, he learns the truth: Shiva and Bhaskaran are now friends and the whole fight was just a drama set by Nallathambi, Shiva supports their marriage. Under Shiva and Bhaskaran's orders, a disappointed Shanmugasundaram is forced to unite Bhaskaran and Chandrika. In the end, it is revealed that the director called Shiva and told him to stop fighting and unite Bhaskaran and Chandrika.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Arya (actor)|Arya]] as Bhaskaran\n* [[Nayantara]] as Chandrika\n* [[Santhanam (actor)|Santhanam]] as \"Thala Thalapathy\" Nallathambi\n* [[Subbu Panchu Arunachalam|Subbu Panchu]] as Saravanan\n* [[Chitra Lakshmanan]] as Shanmugasundaram/mongoose mandaiya\n* [[Rajendran]] as Velpandi\n* [[Ashvin Raja]] as Paalpandi\n* [[Vijayalakshmi (Kannada actress)|Vijaylakshmi]] as Nandhini Saravanan\n* [[Lakshmi Ramakrishnan]] as Sivakami\n* [[Swaminathan]] as Matured Student\n* Monisha  as Nithya\n* [[Poorni]] as Annapoorani\n* [[Jiiva]] in a [[guest appearance]] as [[Siva Manasula Sakthi|Shiva]]\n* [[Shakeela]] as Parimala (guest appearance)\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\nThe film was officially launched on 19 November 2009 at the [[AVM Studios]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/gallery/Events/20146.html |title=Events \u2013 'Boss Engira Baskaran' Movie Launch |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=19 November 2009 |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> with the film starting shooting in December first week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/fullstory.php?id=14920455 |title=Arya\u2019s Boss Engira Bhaskaran launched!|publisher=Sify |date=20 November 2009 |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> Rajesh, following his [[sleeper hit]] ''[[Siva Manasula Sakthi]]'', decided to make another comedy film and to cast [[Arya (actor)|Arya]], who appeared in a cameo role in ''Siva Manasula Sakthi'', in the titular role,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/50850.html |title=Arya is Boss aka Baskaran \u2013 Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> while [[Jiiva]] in return would make a cameo appearance in the film.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.southdreamz.com/2010/04/jeevas-reciprocations-for-boss.html |title=Jeeva's reciprocations for 'Boss' |publisher=Southdreamz.com |date=10 April 2010 |accessdate=4 August 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111009183456/http://www.southdreamz.com/2010/04/jeevas-reciprocations-for-boss.html |archive-date=9 October 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> As the film's backdrop is set to be both village as well as city, the film was shot at various location including [[Thanjavur]], [[Mysore]] and [[Tiruchirappalli|Trichy]].<ref name=shoot>{{cite news|last=V Lakshmi|title=Director Rajesh gets talking to Whatt\u2019\u2019s Hot on his upcoming project Boss Engira Baskaran.....|url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Archive&Source=Page&Skin=TOINEW&BaseHref=TOICH%2F2010%2F08%2F06&ViewMode=GIF&PageLabel=30&EntityId=Ar03002&AppName=1|accessdate=12 March 2014|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]}}</ref> A major part of the film was filmed at [[Kumbakonam]], while a few scenes were shot in [[Chennai]] as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/52594.html |title=Nayantara is with \u2018Boss Engira Baskaran\u2019! - Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/jan-10-01/nayanthara-boss-engira-baskaran-08-01-10.html |title=Nayan moves to Chennai |publisher=Behindwoods |date=8 January 2010 |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> Shooting was also carried on in the [[Swiss Alps]], where some song sequences were picturized.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14946085 |title=Arya & Nayan goes to Swiss Alps|publisher=Sify |date=21 June 2010 |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://chennaionline.com/movies/preview/Aarya-and-Nayantara-to-romance-in-Switzerland/20103925013912.col |title=Aarya and Nayantara to romance in Switzerland &#124; preview \u2013 Movies |publisher=ChennaiOnline |date=25 June 2010 |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> Principal photography ended on 3 August 2010 with the completion of the last song that was canned at a set erected at [[Buckingham and Carnatic Mills|Binny Mills]] near [[Chennai]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14952026 |title=Boss Engira Bhaskaran shoot is complete|publisher=Sify |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> Arya revealed that the script went through changes during production, with Rajesh eventually opting not to include portions where Bhaskaran's brother gets killed in the film. Instead of implementing a revenge script, Rajesh chose to make it a full-length comedy.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xjzbu0-et-0</ref>\n\nWhile Vasan Visual Ventures that produced Arya's ''[[Naan Kadavul]]'', produced this film as well, Arya purchased the rights in the midst to release it under his own production banner \"The Show People\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/58265.html |title=Arya buys over \u2018Boss Engira Baskaran\u2019 - Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> The film's distribution rights, however, were again acquired by Red Giant Movies, led by [[Udhayanidhi Stalin]], who would enact the lead role in Rajesh's next project.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/58980.html |title=Red Giant acquires Boss Engira Bhaskaran \u2013 Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Boss Engira Bhaskaran\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 27 August 2010\n| recorded   = 2009\u20132010\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 23:03\n| label      = [[Think Music India|Think Music]]\n| producer   = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| prev_title = [[Naan Mahaan Alla (2010 film)|Naan Mahaan Alla]]\n| prev_year  = 2010\n| next_title = [[Pathinaaru]]\n| next_year  = 2010\n}}\n\nFollowing the success of ''[[Siva Manasula Sakthi]]'', [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] composed the musical score and soundtrack of ''Boss Engira Bhaskaran'', too.<ref name=\"indiaglitz1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/55770.html |title=\u2018Boss\u2019 gets ready \u2013 Tamil Movie News |publisher=IndiaGlitz |accessdate=4 August 2010}}</ref> The soundtrack album, which was released on 27 August 2010 at Sathyam Cinemas,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14954826 |title=Suriya launches Boss Engira Baskaran audio|publisher=Sify |date=28 August 2010 |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref> contains 5 tracks, featuring lyrics penned by [[Na. Muthukumar]]. The soundtrack received positive response.\n\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Tracklist\n| extra_column    = Singer(s)\n| total_length    = 23:03\n| title1          = Ada Boss Boss\n| extra1          = [[Sathyan (singer)|Sathyan]]\n| length1         = 3:58\n| title2          = Yaar Intha Penthan\n| extra2          = [[Haricharan (singer)|Haricharan]]\n| length2         = 5:01\n| title3          = Thathi Thaavum Paper Naan\n| extra3          = [[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]]\n| length3         = 4:44\n| title4          = Iyley Iyley\n| extra4          = [[Vijay Prakash]]\n| length4         = 5:04\n| title5          = Mama Mama\n| extra5          = Vijay Yesudas, [[Shweta Mohan]]\n| length5         = 4:16\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe satellite rights of the film were secured by [[Kalaignar TV|Kalaignar]]. The film was given a \"U\" certificate by the [[Indian Censor Board]]. In November 2011, it was shown at the International Tamil Film Festival held in Uglich, Russia, alongside ''[[Thillana Mohanambal]]'' (1968), ''[[Chandramukhi]]'' (2005), ''[[Sivaji (film)|Sivaji]]'' (2007), ''[[Angadi Theru]]'' (2010), ''[[Thenmerku Paruvakaatru]]'' (2010) and ''[[Ko (film)|Ko]]'' (2011).<ref>http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/taste-of-sivaji-magic-for-russian-film-buffs/article2513543.ece</ref>  The film was eventually dubbed into [[Telugu language|Telugu]] as ''Nene Ambani'' which released on 17 December 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.sulekha.com/nene-ambani_telugu_movie_release-date |title=Nene Ambani Release Date&#124;Nene Ambani Telugu Movie Releasing Date&#124;Arya&#124;Nayantara&#124;Santhanam&#124; |publisher=Movies.sulekha.com |date=17 December 2010 |accessdate=8 November 2012}}</ref>\n\n=== Box office ===\n''Boss Engira Bhaskaran'' sold 7.3 million tickets worldwide. It released on [[Eid ul-Fitr|Eid]] day, the end of [[Ramadan]], opening across 240 screens in [[Tamil Nadu]] with reportedly 95.5% average theatre occupancy, which, according to trade sources, was the best ever first day opening for Arya then,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14956576 |title=Boss Engira Baskaran- Super Opening|publisher=Sify |date=13 September 2010 |accessdate=8 November 2012}}</ref> which resulted in an increase of the number of shows and screens.<ref name=\"240screens\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-09-13/news-interviews/28235592_1_screens-release-tamil-film|title=A big fat K\u2019wood opening|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=13 September 2010|accessdate=15 September 2010|first1=Sreedhar|last1=Pillai}}</ref><ref name=\"sify.com\">{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14956894&cid=13525926 |title=Chennai box office (Sep 10 \u2013 12)|publisher=Sify |date=15 September 2010 |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref> In its opening weekend, the film was said to have earned {{INR}}58 lakh in [[Chennai]], as reported by Behindwoods,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-slide-shows/movie-4/top-ten-movies-sep-13/tamil-cinema-topten-movie-boss-engira-baskaran.html |title=Boss Engira Baskaran |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref> while according to [[Sify]].com, it grossed {{INR}}65 lakh.<ref name=\"sify.com\" /> At the end of the second weekend, the film had netted {{INR}}10 crore from 275 screens.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14957364&cid=13525926 |title=Chennai Box-office (Sep 17-19)|publisher=Sify |date=22 September 2010 |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref>\n\n=== Critical response ===\nBoss Engira Bhaskaran received positive reviews upon release. ''[[Sify]]'' stated that \"Rajesh has pulled off the impossible, making a family comedy work a second time armed with nothing more than a few situational gaffes and couple of funny dialogues. It\u2019s pure escapist fare and will work big time, as there is paucity of healthy entertainment for the family audiences.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/boss-engira-bhaskaran-review-tamil-14956349.html |title=Movie Review:Boss Engira Bhaskaran|publisher=Sify |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref> ''Indiaglitz'' wrote \"Rajesh has made spoof of some contemporary Tamil films in an enjoyable manner.\" and \"''Boss Engira Baskaran'' is right there oozing with abundant energy and unlimited fun. Kudos to Udhayanidhi for choosing quality films with varied stories that leave an impression with the masses.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/review/11695.html |title=Boss Engira Baskaran Tamil Movie Review |publisher=IndiaGlitz |date=10 September 2010 |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref> ''Chennai Online'' specially pointed out the plus points of the film \"The comic scenes aided by dialogues and the bonding between the two friends are a huge plus and reason enough to see the movie. The casting of each character has been aptly done with no room for excess anywhere making for one smooth ride all through. Nayan and Arya make an adequate pair though there are no great sparks of chemistry between them. However Nayan does make a pretty picture throughout.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chennaionline.com/movies/movie-reviews/20105310055327/Movie-Review-Boss-Engira-Baskaran.col |title=Movie Review: 'Boss Engira Baskaran' &#124; Movie Review \u2013 Movies |publisher=ChennaiOnline |date=10 September 2010 |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref>\n\n''Behindwoods'' gave 2.5 out of 5 and expressed that \"Director Rajesh might just pull it off this time too because he\u2019s got everything right for a comic caper. He also efficiently camouflages the saggy little portions in both the halves of his movie with crisply written dialogues. Perfect for a weekend in which you decide not to give your brain much work.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-2/boss-engira-baskaran-movie-review.html |title=Boss Engira Baskaran Movie Review \u2013 Tamil Movie Boss Engira Baskaran Movie Review |publisher=Behindwoods |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref> A critic from the ''[[Times of India]]'' gave 3 out of 5 and praised the film saying \"When the director shows Boss watching 'Annamalai' on TV and getting inspired, you are not surprised. But his excuses, when facing various career options, make Boss an original. The tutorial college angle may be predictable, but soon humour is back on track, and it is enjoyable. You will also come away with some amazing performances.\"<ref>{{cite news| url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/movie-reviews/Boss-Engira-Bhaskaran/movie-review/6547029.cms | work=The Times of India | title=Boss Engira Bhaskaran | date=10 September 2010}}</ref>\n\n=== Awards ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year!! Award !! Category!! Character !! Cast\n|-\n| 2011 || [[Vijay Awards]] || Best Comedian  || Nallathambi || Santhanam\n|}\n\n== Legacy ==\nThe dialogue \"Nanbenda\" spoken by Santhanam in the film became famous and went viral after the release. The dialogue has inspired a film of [[Nannbenda|same name]]. \"The title, which means friend, was apt because it's a story about two friends. So we felt it will make sense to use it,\" the film's director Jagadish said. Jagadish is the former associate of filmmaker Rajesh.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/regional/south-follows-bollywood-popular-dialogues-songs-inspire-film-titles/article1-1281682.aspx |title=South follows Bollywood: Popular dialogues, songs inspire film titles |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=2014-12-28 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141112182610/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/regional/south-follows-bollywood-popular-dialogues-songs-inspire-film-titles/article1-1281682.aspx |archivedate=12 November 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Another term used by Santhanam in the film, \"Appatakkar\" ([[Know-it-all|know-all]]) also gained popularity.<ref>http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Therikavidalama-to-Senjiduven-Quirky-Kwood-dialogues/articleshow/49337190.cms</ref><ref>http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/Tamil-is-semma-gethu-language-machi/articleshow/50884605.cms</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|3}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|1606183}}\n\n{{M. Rajesh}}\n{{The Show People}}\n\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Tiruchirappalli]]\n[[Category:2010s romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n[[Category:Tamil films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Films directed by M. Rajesh]]\n", "name_user": "Jellysandwich0", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boss_Engira_Bhaskaran"}
